\f4\i Gavor/Ghav
\f2\i0  is the name of the planet, that is, of the entire world. Commonly used to indicate all land, seen or unseen, whether planetary astro-geography is understood or not.  In other words, all places that are not ocean. The world name is often rendered as 
\f4\i Gavor-Havorra
\f2\i0  or 
\f4\i Ghav-Avorr
\f2\i0 , indicating all the lands and seas. When used in an astro-cosmological sense, then just 
\f4\i Gavor/Ghav
\f2\i0  or 
\f4\i Gavoran/Ghavan
\f2\i0  is more typical. (Also see 
\f4\i Havorra
\f2\i0 )
