\f3\i\b Settan
\f2\i0\b0 \
The southern of two major river systems in 
\f4\i Saskantinon
\f2\i0 . With its main source in the high mountains to the west of the Weir Lands, the 
\f4\i Settan
\f2\i0  runs through the entire Saskan Lands from west to east, with many small tributaries feeding into it. The 
\f4\i Settan
\f2\i0  fills the Great Bye Lake, then continues through its natural course to the 
\f4\i Krbsh
\f2\i0  Sea. Saskan provinces south of the 
\f4\i Settan
\f2\i0  are called the Settan Lands, where the river is the object of veneration for many river-centered ideologies/theologies/belief systems widespread in those provinces.\
\

\f3\i\b sint
\f2\i0\b0 \
Sentient beings with non-human phenotype, who obviously have some non-human DNA mixed into their genotype.\
\

\f4\i Sints
\f2\i0  vary a great deal in appearance. Some have very human-like features with only a few minor characteristics of their non-huum DNA apparent. Others are very distinctly non-human. Due to the modifications made and significant amounts of human DNA used to adapt brain size, larynx and, often, coding of extremities to develop fine motor skills, it is very unusual for 
\f4\i sints
\f2\i0  to be indistinguishable or largely indistinguishable from  their non-sentient ancestors. (Also see 
\f4\i beest
\f2\i0 , 
\f4\i fon
\f2\i0 , 
\f4\i rip
\f2\i0 , and 
\f4\i ixh
\f2\i0 )\
\

\f1\b Untamed
\f2\b0 \
The term "Untamed" was originally used pejoratively by 
\f4\i huum
\f2\i0  opposed to viewing 
\f4\i sints
\f2\i0  as equals. It was intended to cast 
\f4\i sints
\f2\i0  as Other, wild, violent, dangerous and so on. Over the centuries, it was adopted by 
\f4\i sints
\f2\i0  themselves as an ironic label and now carries little emotional weight; it just means "a 
\f4\i sint
\f2\i0  organization".  (Also see: 
\f4\i sint
\f2\i0 )\
\
Within the Saskan Lands are a wide variety of 
\f4\i sint
\f2\i0  organizations, often organized along species lines.  They vary in purpose.  Most practice self-defense, community mutual aid, dialogue and cooperation with 
\f4\i huum
\f2\i0  or with other 
\f4\i sint
\f2\i0  communities, promote training and education, and so on.  Others are more radical, some revolutionary, a few are violently anti-
\f4\i huum
\f2\i0 . These political groups follow a bewildering brew of ideologies.   \
